Class Dyad

  • java.lang.Object
    • Dyad
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DyadTemp

    public class Dyad
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable
    A Dyad is a pair of Individuals who have a named relationship; this class captures all the information we need about any particular dyad in order to compare it with other dyads or with library definitions.
    See Also:

    • Field Detail

      • level

        public int level
        Level means the generation of Alter in Ego's family tree. 0 = Ego's level; 1 = Ego's parents' level, -1 = Ego's kids' level, etc. This has the same meaning as treelevel in Node and Variable, or as level in ClauseBody.

      • kinTerm

        public java.lang.String kinTerm
        kinTerm is the name of the relationship between Ego and Alter.

      • kinTermType

        public int kinTermType
        kinTermType is PRIMARY (0), or EXTENDED(1). Code of 7 indicates a dyad created by special request of the Learner.

      • addrOrRef

      • path

      • pcString

        public java.lang.String pcString
        pcString is a concatenation of all the link-types followed along the path between Ego and Alter. For example: if Alter is Ego's paternal grandfather, the pcString would be "FaFa".

      • pcStringStructural

        public java.lang.String pcStringStructural
        pcStringStructural is a concatenation of the gender-neutral link-types followed between Ego and Alter. For example: if Alter is Ego's paternal grandfather, the pcStringStructural would contain 2 "P" links. Valid link-types are "P" (parent), "C" (child), "S" (spouse), and "*" (star-link).

      • confirmed

        public boolean confirmed
        confirmed = true means User has confirmed this Dyad is reliable. Ergo, it should not be treated as an Anomaly. challenged = true means this dyad has been added to an Anomaly

      • challenged

        public boolean challenged
        confirmed = true means User has confirmed this Dyad is reliable. Ergo, it should not be treated as an Anomaly. challenged = true means this dyad has been added to an Anomaly
